In a medium-size bowl, mix mayonnaise and vinegar; mix in cheese and green onions. Spread a third of the filling over half of each tortilla. Fold plain half of tortilla over to cover filling. Lightly brown quesadillas in a wide nonstick frying pan over medium heat (3 to 5 minutes); turn carefully and brown other sides (2 to 3 more minutes). Cut each into 4 triangles.